        "Draw the four stages of mitosis (prophase, metaphase, anaphase, telophase) in a sequence of four cell diagrams. In each diagram, show: chromosome condensation state, nuclear envelope state, spindle fibre arrangement, and chromosome position. Add cytokinesis as a fifth diagram showing the cleavage furrow (animal) or cell plate (plant).",
        "Draw a GPCR signalling cascade in a linear flow diagram: Ligand → GPCR → Gαs (GDP→GTP) → Adenylyl cyclase → cAMP ↑ → PKA (inactive→active) → Substrate phosphorylation → Cellular response. Annotate at each enzymatic step how many molecules are produced per activation event (amplification). Indicate where phosphodiesterase terminates the signal."
