        "PCR primer design practice: given a 500 bp genomic target sequence, design a forward and reverse primer (18–22 nt each, 50–60% GC content, Tm ~58–62°C, no self-complementarity). Calculate the expected product size. Identify the annealing temperature for the PCR protocol. Verify that both primers amplify only the target (check for off-target complementarity in the flanking sequence provided)."
