        "For chemoreceptor stimuli: 'Central CO₂, Carotid O₂' — Central chemoreceptors (medulla) primarily respond to CO₂/pH; Carotid bodies (peripheral) primarily respond to low O₂ (PaO₂ <60 mmHg). The alliteration C-C-C-C aids recall."
