        "Spirometry pattern identification drill: given five sets of FEV₁ (% predicted), FVC (% predicted), and FEV₁/FVC, classify each as: normal, obstructive, restrictive, or mixed. For each abnormal result, identify the likely disease category and the physiological mechanism. Track errors and repeat the disease categories most frequently misclassified until 5/5 correct without reference."
