        "Draw the parallel timelines of oogenesis and spermatogenesis side by side. For oogenesis: oogonium (foetal) → primary oocyte arrested Prophase I (foetal–puberty) → secondary oocyte arrested Metaphase II (ovulation) → mature oocyte (fertilisation). For spermatogenesis: spermatogonium → primary spermatocyte → secondary spermatocyte → spermatid → spermatozoon (continuous). At each arrow, write the ploidy change and what event triggers the transition.",
