        "Make a card for each phase of the menstrual cycle: front = phase name and days; back = dominant hormone(s), ovarian event, uterine event, what ends this phase. Create a separate card for the LH surge with: trigger conditions (oestrogen >200 pg/mL for >36 h), feedback type (positive), consequence (ovulation within 36–38 hours), and what happens to the follicle afterwards (luteinisation → corpus luteum).",
        "Make a fertilisation event sequence card set: one card per event. Front = event name (e.g. capacitation, acrosome reaction, cortical reaction); back = molecular mediator, what triggers it, what it achieves, and its clinical/pharmacological relevance. Review as a sequence — shuffle the cards and place them in correct chronological order as a self-test.",
        "Make a 'common mistakes' card set for reproductive physiology: front = incorrect statement; back = correction + memory anchor. Key cards: 'Mature egg released at ovulation' → secondary oocyte, Metaphase II arrest; 'LH surge is negative feedback' → positive feedback from high sustained oestrogen; 'hCG = LH' → LH mimic from trophoblast, not from pituitary; 'Luteal phase varies between women' → follicular phase varies; luteal phase is fixed at ~14 days."
