        "Create a five-column bone cell comparison table. Rows: osteogenic cell, osteoblast, osteocyte, osteoclast. Columns: (1) lineage origin; (2) location in bone; (3) primary function; (4) identifying marker molecules; (5) response to PTH and oestrogen. Fill every cell — no blanks. Self-test by covering columns 2–5 and reconstructing from the cell name alone.",
